{
  "stem": "19502.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Ukrainian I spoke, so we learned Ukrainian and Russian.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we did add Yiddish, but as a language, I think, once or twice a week.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We did have.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, soldiers coming and going all the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we weren't very happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this was not all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was only for about three, four months till it established a front, you know, on the other side of the Bug.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then, they brought us some refugees, you see, which no country took them in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they ran away from the other side.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, like Poland is the Bug is the river.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when they ran away from the German occupation, they're running on the Russian side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Russians brought-- accepted them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They send them later on Donbass, which is in the mines, in the coal mines, and send them [INAUDIBLE] said, we did send them all over to work, which is-- I think it's legitimate.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those, they say, thought it was crime.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It don't a crime to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But you see they brought them in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And if you want to or not, this is, look, now we're bringing in 10 people, 15 people, whatever it is, you have to house the people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were Polish refugees.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, Jewish from Poland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know which they ran by the occupy Germany, which they managed to run away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were in Russia, you see.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they, later, they send them to Donbass, which is the-- the-- the coal mines to work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were treated wonderful because, I mean, at least they weren't killed, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They ran.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And like in our house, every few days we had different people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes, they'd stay for a week or two.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
